<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRUNK STUDY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * The Department of Transportation needs $370,000 to figure out why a drunk 
person is more likely to be hit by a car than a sober person (Dec. 28). Is this 
really a mystery? It might be time for another tea party, folks. 
</P>
<P>
 DAVID E. SCOTT 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
