<HEADLINE>
<P>
NHL ROUNDUP; ROY, DAMPHOUSSE LEAD CANADIENS, 3-1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Patrick Roy made 25 saves and Vincent Damphousse scored the winning goal as 
the Montreal Canadiens beat the Washington Capitals, 3-1, on Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Eric Desjardins scored in the first period, Damphousse in the second and 
Gilbert Dionne in the third for Montreal, which had lost two in a row. 
</P>
<P>
 The Canadiens limited Washington to only 12 shots through the first two 
periods, but Dmitri Khristich scored on Washington's first shot of the final 
period. 
</P>
<P>
 Boston 5, Hartford 3 -- Cam Neely scored a tie-breaking goal late in the third 
period as the Bruins maintained their Boston Garden dominance over the Whalers. 
</P>
<P>
 The Whalers have not beaten the Bruins in Boston Garden in 13 games since Nov. 
12, 1990. 
</P>
<P>
 San Jose 3, Calgary 2 -- Todd Elik's second goal of the game broke a 
third-period tie and lifted the Sharks over the Flames at San Jose, earning the 
Sharks their franchise-record 40th point of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 Detroit 6, Tampa Bay 3 -- Ray Sheppard scored twice and assisted on goals by 
Steve Yzerman and Paul Coffey when the Red Wings took advantage of Tampa Bay 
special-teams breakdowns to beat the Lightning at Minneapolis. 
</P>
<P>
 Florida 2, N.Y. Islanders 1 -- Mark Fitzpatrick, a former Islander, made a 
triumphant return to Long Island, stopping 34 shots as the Florida Panthers 
topped the .500 mark for the first time in franchise history with a win over 
the Islanders at Uniondale, N.Y. 
</P>
