<HEADLINE>
<P>
UCLA RISES TO NO. 2 IN THE AP POLL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UCLA, one of only two remaining unbeaten NCAA Division I teams, moved to 
second in the Associated Press poll that was released Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bruins (11-0) are tied for first with Kansas in the USA Today/CNN poll, 
which was released Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 However, Kansas, No. 1 in the AP poll, suffered a 68-64 loss to Kansas State 
on Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The Jayhawks (16-2) received 29 first-place votes and 1,552 points from the 
national media panel to edge UCLA, which was first on 26 ballots and had 1,514 
points. Kansas is the fourth team to sit atop the rankings this season, joining 
North Carolina, Kentucky and Arkansas. 
</P>
<P>
 The only other unbeaten Division I team, St. Louis (14-0), broke into the AP 
top 25 for the first time since the 1964-65 season, when the Billikens got as 
high as fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Louis is No. 23. 
</P>
