<P>
LONG BEACH LOSES, 92-69; GREENBERG EJECTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It is tough to beat Pacific at home, and Long Beach State tried to do it 
Monday night without Coach Seth Greenberg on the bench in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 The 49ers lost, 92-69. 
</P>
<P>
 Greenberg picked up his second technical foul and was ejected with 21 seconds 
left to intermission for yelling at the officials. 
</P>
<P>
 Greenberg's absence may not have mattered anyway, since Pacific led 54-32 at 
halftime following a 21-8 run. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory for Pacific, 9-7 overall and 3-2 in the Big West Conference, was 
its 10th in a row at home. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach (8-4, 3-2) cut the margin to 56-39 with 17:22 to play but could get 
no closer. 
</P>
<P>
 Terrance O'Kelley scored a career-high 25 points for Long Beach and Eric Brown 
had 13. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Jackson scored 24 points to lead Pacific. 
</P>
