<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES: DANA HILLS' COVINGTON COMMITS TO MIAMI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Scott Covington, a quarterback from Dana Hills High, has made an oral 
commitment to attend Miami, former Dana Hills Coach Jack Murry said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Covington, a first-team All-South Coast League selection, completed 58% of his 
passes for more than 1,700 yards last season. 
</P>
<P>
 "Obviously, it's a great opportunity," Covington said. "I'll get to play for a 
team that can contend for the national championship every year." 
</P>
<P>
 The 6-foot-4, 180-pound senior was a preseason Superprep magazine Far-West 
All-American and chose the Hurricanes over Alabama, Wisconsin, USC and 
Washington State. 
</P>
<P>
 Miami Coach Dennis Erickson came to the Covington residence Dec. 1, the first 
day coaches could visit recruits. 
</P>
<P>
 "I guess that shows I was important to them," Covington said. "They have a 
situation where they need a quarterback and they need one quick. I'm very 
excited." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 David Schuetz, a 6-4, 225-pound outside linebacker from Dana Hills, made an 
oral commitment to Oregon, Murry said. Schuetz was a first-team All-South Coast 
selection in 1992, but played in only one game last season after breaking his 
leg. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Terry Williams of El Dorado, a 6-6, 260-pound offensive lineman who was 
first-team Times All-Orange County, will attend UCLA, he said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Williams, chose UCLA over USC, Colorado, California and Arizona State. Former 
Esperanza standout Travis Kirschke, the 1992 Times Orange County lineman of the 
year, hosted Williams' visit to UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
 "I played against Travis and I grew up loving the Bruins," Williams said. 
Steve Williams, Terry's brother, played for UCLA from 1980-84. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Darryl Jones, a first-team All-Division X offensive lineman from Brethren 
Christian, made an oral commitment to Washington State, Brethren Christian 
Coach Ken Sharrar said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones, 6-3, 295, earned All-Olympic honors the last two seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Mitch McCrimmon, a first-team all-county offensive lineman from Capistrano 
Valley, made an oral commitment to Villanova, Capistrano Valley Coach Eric 
Patton said. 
</P>
<P>
 McCrimmon, who is 6-6, 270 pounds, earned first-team Division I and first-team 
All-South Coast League honors. He chose the Wildcats, who play in Division 
I-AA, over New Mexico and San Diego State. 
</P>
<P>
 Teammate Levi Roquemore, a 6-1, 225-pound linebacker who earned second-team 
all-county honors, made an oral commitment to New Mexico, Patton said. 
</P>
<P>
 Roquemore, an All-South Coast selection the past two seasons, chose New Mexico 
over Fresno State and Villanova. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Brad and Brian Finneran of Santa Margarita, both first-team all-county 
selections, made oral commitments to Villanova, their brother Baron confirmed 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Brad, an all-county defensive back, had a county-leading seven interceptions. 
Brian, an all-county wide receiver, finished his career with an all-time Orange 
County-record 178 receptions. Only John McKay, of USC and La Puente Bishop 
Amat, caught more passes (207) in section history. MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
