<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: BRASILIA; PAYING THE PIPER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An investigative panel probing corruption in the Brazilian legislature is 
scheduled to release its final report Saturday, and at least two dozen 
lawmakers are facing near certain expulsion from congress. 
</P>
<P>
 The report concludes a nearly four-month investigation into a huge kickback 
and influence-peddling scheme in which ranking members of the congressional 
budget committee allegedly pocketed millions of dollars of taxpayers' money in 
exchange for writing budget items favoring pet projects for select politicians 
and businesses. 
</P>
<P>
 The panel is expected to recommend censure or expulsion of up to 30 
legislators, who may later face criminal charges. A separate investigation into 
alleged misdeeds by construction companies is also scheduled to get underway in 
the next few months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
