OFF THE TICKER: WANTED: TALENT FOR TURF BATTLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 College students casting about for careers might want to consider turf science 
-- not the art of handicapping horses but the care and maintenance of golf 
courses. 
</P>
<P>
 Turf science majors at Purdue University have all found jobs upon graduation 
over the past eight years, according to Purdue agronomy professor Clark 
Throssell. 
</P>
<P>
 And there's room for advancement, the university suggests in a newsletter 
listing job possibilities -- but only for grads whose grass is always greener. 
