<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 2; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
97 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Blockbuster Buys Share in Virgin Entertainment Software: Blockbuster 
Entertainment Corp., awaiting a merger with Viacom Inc., issued $30 million 
worth of new stock to buy a 20% stake in Virgin Interactive Entertainment, 
which develops and publishes video games for the Nintendo and Sega game 
systems.Virgin Interactive is part of the Virgin airline and entertainment 
empire run by British entrepreneur Richard Branson. The Fort Lauderdale, 
Fla.-based video rental company will be able to profit by licensing new 
products through its Spelling and Republic studio holdings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA011894-0104 </DOCNO>
