<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: GENERAL AUTOMATION INC. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Anaheim computer company reported a loss of $577,000, or 5 cents a share, 
for its fiscal year ended Sept. 30.Those results, which included a $994,000 
loss on the sale of its European operations, contrasted with a profit of 
$144,000, or 1 cent a share, for the previous year. Sales declined 5% to $42.9 
million from $45.2 million. For its fourth fiscal quarter, the company lost $1 
million, or 9 cents a share, compared to a loss of $240,000, or 2 cents a 
share, for the same period a year earlier. Three-month sales were $10.4 
million, up slightly from $10.2 million. 
</P>
