<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: DIVISION HEAD NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Lockheed executive was selected Friday to head the defense company's CalComp 
Inc. computer graphics division, replacing William Conlin, who left in November 
after 10 years as president. 
</P>
<P>
 Gary R. Long succeeds Conlin as head of the 1,600-employee division. CalComp 
makes computer graphics peripheral equipment, such as plotters and digitizers, 
which are used to print complex graphics like engineering drawings. 
</P>
<P>
 Long will report to Val P. Peline, president of Lockheed's electronic systems 
group, who headed CalComp temporarily while a search for Conlin's replacement 
took place. Long was formerly president of CalComp's digitizer division in 
Scottsdale, Ariz. 
</P>
<P>
 James R. Bell, vice president of the digitizer division, will become the 
division's president. 
</P>
</TEXT>
