<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: CLINTON REPORT CARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Complied by Susan Christian, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Did President Clinton earn passing grades for his first year in office? 
</P>
<P>
 About 200 Orange County business people will have an opportunity to register 
their opinions at "Bill Clinton's First Anniversary Report Card," sponsored by 
UCI Graduate School of Management.The event will be Thursday, one year after 
the President's inauguration. 
</P>
<P>
 Richard McKenzie, a UCI economist who specializes in government policy, will 
open the program with his own evaluation. He wouldn't provide a sneak preview 
saying, "I don't want to give away the punch line." 
</P>
<P>
 Rather than reading, 'riting and 'rithmetic, Clinton will be graded on 
leadership, economic growth, health care and international trade policies. 
</P>
<P>
 The two-hour event begins at 7:30 a.m. and includes breakfast. It will take 
place at the Arnold & Mabel Beckman Center, next to the UCI campus. Cost is 
$20. To order tickets, call (714) 856-5781. 
</P>
</TEXT>
