<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: APPOINT PRESIDENT QUITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Appoint Technologies Inc. said Friday that President and Chief Executive 
Joseph C. Picken has resigned and that the company plans to sell a unit it 
acquired in a merger last April. 
</P>
<P>
 In a release, the Anaheim electronics maker said it may sell Appoint Inc., a 
computer input device manufacturer, back to its founder, John B. Barrett, after 
being unable to raise enough cash to keep the unit afloat. Barrett has also 
resigned as Appoint Technologies' vice chairman, it was announced. 
</P>
<P>
 E.W. Baumgardner, company chairman, will assume the titles of president and 
chief executive, according to a company release. 
</P>
</TEXT>
