<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jerry Hick; Thuan Le, EY, ENCER,; Jeffrey A. Perlman 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ALWAYS READY: When San Francisco suffered an earthquake in 1989, Orange County 
Fire Department battalion chief Chuck Nicola was among the first called to the 
scene. Last year's Hurricane Emily off the Carolina Coast: Nicola was there. So 
no surprise that Nicola, head of the county's 56-member urban search and rescue 
task force, took his whole crew to Northridge after Monday's quake. . . . "He 
wrote the book," says a Fire Department spokeswoman, "so you know where he's 
going to be any time there's an emergency." 
</P>
</TEXT>
