<TEXT>
<P>
 KEEPING TRACK: By April, the number of commuter trains heading north and south 
out of Orange County is going to triple.Which is why officials are worried 
about youngsters playing on or near the railroad tracks. The County 
Transportation Authority has begun putting on train-related safety 
demonstrations in county schools, to run through the end of May. . . . "Kids 
are fascinated by trains," says authority board member Irv Pickler. "But they 
have to stay away from railroad tracks." 
</P>
