<TEXT>
<P>
 POWER OF LONGEVITY: Conservative political pundit Pat Buchanan took his first 
White House job for Richard Nixon and has been a Nixon loyalist since. He'll be 
on hand Thursday when Nixon returns to his presidential library in Yorba Linda 
to announce a new studies center there. . . . Says Buchanan: "It is natural and 
fitting that the new center will dwell on questions of war and peace." As for 
Nixon's enemies, Buchanan adds: "He has the greatest revenge; he has outlived 
them." 
</P>
