<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; CALTRANS NAMES INTERIM DIRECTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GEOFF BOUCHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 P. Kay Griffin has been named interim director of the California Department of 
Transportation district that encompasses Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 Griffin, 52, replaces Russell O. Lightcap, who retired as the director of 
District 12 in December after 45 years with Caltrans. 
</P>
<P>
 Griffin, an Oklahoma native, has worked for Caltrans since 1965, when she 
became one of only four women among the ranks of the approximately 5,000 
engineers then with the agency. 
</P>
<P>
 Now, she said, there are about 750 women out of 13,000 engineers. 
</P>
<P>
 Calling her first week on the job "stimulating," Griffin said she hopes the 
temporary assignment will be a "growing experience." 
</P>
<P>
 No permanent successor has been named. A formal interview process will be 
conducted to find a replacement. An Orange County Transportation Authority 
representative will participate in the search. 
</P>
<P>
 Caltrans District 12 has direct supervision over $400 million in projects in 
Orange County this year and also has indirect oversight for another $1 billion 
in toll road construction and other projects. 
</P>
<P>
 In a previous assignment, Griffin was chief of the Division of Highway 
Operations, giving her responsibility for setting statewide policy and 
standards for the state highway system, toll bridges, ride-sharing facilities 
and truck operations.GEOFF BOUCHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
