<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: DANA POINT; PUBLIC MEETING ON RESORT TO BE ON TV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The first of four public workshops on the controversial $500-million resort 
planned for the Headlands will be broadcast live tonight at 6 p.m. on local 
Channel 30. 
</P>
<P>
 John Ballew, the city's consultant on the project, will make a presentation 
and take questions from the City Council. No public testimony will be allowed. 
</P>
<P>
 As currently proposed, the resort plan includes a 400-room hotel and 394 homes 
along the 121-acre bluff-top parcel overlooking Dana Point Harbor. The plan has 
been approved by the city Planning Commission and is now under review by the 
council. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshops will continue every other Tuesday evening through March 1. 
Tonight's workshop is scheduled to end at 8. 
</P>
</TEXT>
