<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOST SUPERIOR COURTS CLOSED TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles Superior Court officials announced Monday that many criminal and 
civil Superior Courts will be closed today, including those Downtown and in Van 
Nuys, Santa Monica, San Fernando, the Mid-City area and Lancaster. 
</P>
<P>
 Other Superior Courts, including Torrance and Norwalk, were scheduled to open. 
</P>
<P>
 The closure in Van Nuys means there will be no deliberations today in the Lyle 
Menendez murder trial. 
</P>
<P>
 "How long we're going to be closed, I don't know," said Superior Court Judge 
Robert Letteau, supervising judge of the Van Nuys Courthouse. 
</P>
</TEXT>
